  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\choice.function:on{X}]\nDescribes: f(x__) ::= y_\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nspecifies:\n. x__ \"in\" X\n. y_ is \\set\nDocumented:\n. called: \"choice function on $X?$\"\n. written: \"f?\"\n. description: \"A choice function on a collection $X$ of sets is a function $f \\colon X \\to \\bigcup_{A \\in X} A$ such that $f(A) \\in A$ for every $A \\in X$. It selects one element from each set in the collection.\"\nId: \"b557b79f-5179-4fff-a20f-a93d742231a4\"",
